<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0822 </DOCNO><TEXT>Hydropower is important for the sawing industry. At the present electricitycost of 7 to 12 DM/m/sup 3/ of cut wood, hydroelectric power is quitecompetitive. The hydropower technology, its main operating regimes (direktdrive, autonomous operation, synchronous or asynchronous to the network)with their advantages and shortcomings, and the modernisation of olderplants are gone into. Also discussed are modifications of the hydraulicelements, efficiency enhancement, simplification of control, conversionto belt drives or gearbox drives; prevention of flooding, energy conservationand turbine automation. Economic considerations are presented, and investmentcriteria are indicated. (HWJ).</TEXT></DOC>